 to be real, whether it is possible to experience them, and in which sense we can speak about their objective validity. These topics – which were also discussed by early phenomenologists like Brentano, Meinong, Ehrenfels, proponents of Gestalt psychology like Köhler, by Husserl, and by French phenomenologists like Merleau-Ponty – are approached by both historical and systematic analysis.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aOntology. 0aValues. 4aBrentano. 4aHusserl. 4aMeinong. 4aMerleau-Ponty. 7aPHILOSOPHY / History & Surveys / General.2bisacsh1 aBagnoli, Carla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBertolini, Mara Meletti, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCenti, Beatrice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCenti, Beatrice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aChrudzimski, Arkadiusz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuemer, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHuemer, Wolfgang, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPoli, Roberto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReicher, Maria E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aToccafondi, Fiorenza, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVillela-Petit, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Philosophy 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023848808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Philosophy 2000 - 2014z9783110636949o